 – and end recordsetting lapse posted on november   by marideth november   marked the month anniversary of the lapse in congressional authorization of the generalized system of preferences gsp this lapse is now the longest in the year history of the gsp – a fact costing us importers approximately  million every day  million since the july   expiration and that has led to canceled orders from thousands of businesses in gsp countries the  geographically and economically diverse countries of alliance believe that the final months of the th congress are an opportune time for congress to put gsp on its “mustdo” lists either by attaching gsp renewal to other moving bills or by passing s and hr  the urgency of the situation – job losses and business closures in importing and supplying nations especially among small and mediumsized businesses – is clear the alliance cites an important example maria roseni alvero commercial counselor in the philippines embassy pointed out that “in the case of philippine coconut farmers in the typhoon haiyanaffected areas they have become even more reliant on gsp so that they can export competitively to the us market resuming operation of gsp is a key factor to aid in their recovery from the devastation caused by the super typhoon” the kyrgyz republic and lebanon recently joined the alliance to request gsp renewal in   of lebanon’s exports to the us market entered under gsp lebanese businesses have been especially affected since the gsp lapse lebanon’s exports entering under gsp dropped  in  through september as compared to a year earlier examples are lebanon’s jewelry exports down  and exports of building stone nuts gherkins and olive oil items exported in small amounts by lebanon’s farmers artisans and other businesses have decreased by half the gsp lapse creates an urgent situation for the  gsp countries and especially for  nations that benefit from no other us preference program background gsp benefits more than  billion people living in twothirds of the world’s economies when gsp is in operation us companies can import up to  products dutyfree such as raw materials intermediary goods and consumerready items from suppliers in  emerging markets information on the alliance and gsp is available at wwwallianceforgsporg media contacts are romulo cabeza sandler trade llc at rcabezasandlertradecom and marideth sandler at sandlersandlertradecom or at  cell posted in international trade  leave a comment looking to make a difference through international trade join us posted on september   by marideth we are looking for a trade analyst interested in working in a social entrepreneurial firm operating in the intersection of international trade and sustainable business growth in developing economies are you interested in strategic trade analysis working with emerging economies to grow and diversify their exports advocating on the hill or within the administration if so keep reading do you have strong analytical and research skills with experience in trade data tariff information and us regulatory environment would you describe yourself as a creative selfstarter and team player who learns quickly is comfortable working on new issues delivers accurate work within deadlines and can reliably file datespecific required paperwork if so we would very much like to hear from you by wednesday september  please send a cover letter resume and writing sample to sandlersandlertradecom no calls please here’s the full job announcement immediate opening for trade analyst indications of interest due september   about us sandler trade llc is a consulting firm whose goal is to make international trade really happen – especially with emerging economies the firm’s website is httpsandlertradecom position summary sandler trade llc seeks a fulltime trade analyst with a solid trade background and excellent investigative writing and editing skills the analyst works collaboratively within the firm’s team to assist embassies businesses and 