de resume cover letter and writing sample to sandlersandlertradecom by wed sept  no calls please posted in international trade  leave a comment gsp lapse marks its first anniversary – unanticipated costs mount for emerging economies and us importers posted on august   by marideth august   marked the oneyear anniversary of the lapse in congressional authorization of the generalized system of preferences gsp the member alliance of gsp countries has expressed disappointment that congress did not renew gsp prior to leaving washington for its august recess the ongoing lapse in gsp impacts the livelihood of thousands of small and mediumsized businesses in the united states and in gspbeneficiary countries since august   us businesses have paid reinstated import duties for products from gspeligible countries costing us importers  million thus far or approximately  million per day exporters from gspeligible countries have felt the impacts as well us customers have canceled orders from hundreds of businesses in gsp countries and are reconsidering their commercial ties with gsp countries in favor of lowcost producers the lack of gsp not only hurts the bottom line for businesses worldwide and in the united states but also undermines the us strategic goals of deepening economic ties and overall partnerships with developing economies the alliance applauded the bipartisan efforts of the senate and house of representatives trade leadership when they introduced legislation in july  to extend gsp now a year later the continued absence of gsp illustrates the difficulty in finding a viable legislative path the geographically and economically diverse group of alliance countries strongly urges congress to renew gsp when it returns from its august recess gsp provides dutyfree treatment for up to  types of us imports from  emerging economies us imports from gsp beneficiary countries benefit the livelihoods of more than  billion people living in twothirds of the world’s economies gsp also strengthens the us economy by generating tens of thousands of jobs and providing us manufacturers with needed inputs since the expiration american importers have lost sales stopped hiring and delayed expansion plans information on the alliance and gsp is available at wwwallianceforgsporg media contacts romulo cabeza sandler trade llc at rcabezasandlertradecom posted in international trade  leave a comment sandler to give insider’s perspective in guatemala on “how us trade policy is made” posted on may   by marideth ceo and international trade advisor marideth sandler is slated to be one of the lead off speakers at the twoday caftadr forum in antigua guatemala on may    the washington international trade association and george washington university are holding the intensive seminar on the occasion of the tenth anniversary of the uscentral america – dominican republic free trade agreement caftadr the forum to be attended by over  business leaders and government officials is co sponsored by the guatemalan agricultural chamber the guatemalan apparel  textile exporters association and the guatemalan ministry of economy ten years have passed since the agreement was signed caftadr has had a positive impact on international trade for both sides although there is still room to expand economic relations the forum’s purpose is to assist central american and guatemalan firms to better understand the “nuts and bolts” of how us trade policy is made and how us agencies operate ms sandler will speak on “trade responsibilities in the executive branch” as former deputy chief of staff at the office of the us trade representative and now working on behalf of many emergingmarket countries in washington dc she is wellplaced to provide a description of trade policy in the executive branch including “white house agencies eg ustr and nscnec as well as in cabinetlevel agencies eg department of commerce and department of agriculture she will also talk about the more intangible aspects of worki